com.blukii.sdk.info

Class ResolveData

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.blukii.sdk.info.ResolveData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable

    public final class ResolveData
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.os.Parcelable

    Read only data object for resolved output data of the blukii info manager

    ResolveData can be valid for blukii modules only.

    It contains the results of a data request to the blukii Info Manager (https://manager.blukiiinfo.com).
    The ResolveData fields contain the values of one corresponding blukii number.

    ResolveData is part of OutputElement.
    It will be set for the following cases:

    • OutputElement ID (see OutputElement.getId() must be configured as a blukii number on the blukii Info Manager by an Info Manager user. This is an requirement for all BlukiiClient callbacks!

    • ResolveData will be requested during the discovery (see BlukiiClient.initDiscovery(BlukiiClient.OnDiscoveryListener)) for all discovered Elements if the setting ResolveSettings.isResolveEnabled() is set true.
      If some data is responded it will be returned as part of an OutputElement by callback BlukiiClient.OnDiscoveryListener.onDiscoveryResult(ArrayList).
      The result state of resolving can additionally be read by calling OutputElement.getResolveState():
      • UNRESOLVED: Resolve is off (ResolveSettings.isResolveEnabled() is false) or blukii Info Manager is not connectable
      • RESOLVED: blukii Info Manager has responded data for the OutputElement ID
      • NODATA: blukii Info Manager is connectable but has responded no data for the OutputElement ID
      • CACHED: ResolveData contains cached data that has been responded earlier (see cache settings on ResolveSettings)

    • ResolveData will be requested for a single Element by calling (@see BlukiiClient.resolveInputElement(InputElement, BlukiiClient.OnResolveInputElementListener)).
      If some data is responded it will be returned as part of an OutputElement by callback BlukiiClient.OnResolveInputElementListener.onResolveResult(OutputElement).
      The result state of resolving can additionally be read by calling OutputElement.getResolveState(). For single element requests there is no cache available.
      • RESOLVED: blukii Info Manager has responded data for the OutputElement ID
      • NODATA: blukii Info Manager has not responded data for the OutputElement ID
    See Also:
    OutputElement, ResolveSettings, BlukiiClient.initDiscovery(BlukiiClient.OnDiscoveryListener), BlukiiClient.resolveInputElement(InputElement, BlukiiClient.OnResolveInputElementListener)

      • getLanguage

        public java.lang.String getLanguage()
        Gets the output language of the ResolveData set.

        It shows the language specific selection of the blukii number fields getUrl() and getTitle(), for OutputType.PDF also of getUrlExtra() and getPlainTextExtra().

        The output language is chosen by the resolver process. If only one language specific blukii number URL and title is defined it will be returned.
        Otherwise the language is chosen according the language priority setting (see ResolveSettings.getLanguagePriority().

        The value can be one of the following language codes: en-gb, fr-fr or de-de
        Returns:
        language code of the resolved output language
        See Also:
        ResolveSettings.getLanguagePriority()

        public java.lang.String getPlainTextExtra()

      • getRssi

        public short getRssi()
        Gets the value of the blukii number field Visibility range.

        This value contains a Bluetooth module defined value for the rssi range in addition to the global rssi setting (see DiscoverySettings.getRssiThreshold().

        It does not affect the BLE scan itself but is designed for a better output handling.
        Returns:
        Value of blukii number field Visibility range
        See Also:
        DiscoverySettings.getRssiThreshold()

        The language is defined by property getLanguage().

        See Also:

      • getUrl

        public java.lang.String getUrl()
        Gets the value of the language specific blukii number field URL.

        The language is defined by property getLanguage().

        Note: In most cases getUrl returns an url to a OutputType specific file. Exceptions are:
        • OutputType OutputType.MESSAGE: The message text itself will be returned.
        • Resolving single elements of InputSourceType.SCAN by BlukiiClient.resolveInputElement(InputElement, BlukiiClient.OnResolveInputElementListener):
          If you resolve a QR code with format OutputType.WIFI or OutputType.VCARD the WIFI or VCARD formatted code will be returned.
        Returns:
        Value of blukii number field URL
        See Also:
        getLanguage(), OutputType, InputSourceType
